// 🧪 EXEMPLE DE TEST COMPLET - Flux de Trajet Révisé
// Importer dans Postman ou REST Client

###
### SETUP - Créer 2 utilisateurs
###

### 1. Créer Chauffeur (User A)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "chauffeur_test",
  "email": "chauffeur@test.com",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "firstName": "Ahmed",
  "lastName": "Chauffeur",
  "phone": "+221771234567"
}

@driverId = {{response.body.$.id}}
@driverToken = {{response.body.$.accessToken}}

---

### 2. Créer Passager (User B)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "passager_test",
  "email": "passager@test.com",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "firstName": "Marie",
  "lastName": "Passager",
  "phone": "+221771234568"
}

@passagerId = {{response.body.$.id}}
@passengerToken = {{response.body.$.accessToken}}

---

###
### PHASE 1: CRÉATION DU TRAJET
###

### 3. Chauffeur crée trajet
POST http://localhost:3000/rides
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @driverToken

{
  "origin": "Dakar",
  "destination": "Rufisque",
  "originLat": 14.7167,
  "originLng": -17.4677,
  "destLat": 14.8333,
  "destLng": -17.0833,
  "departureDate": "2026-03-20T12:00:00Z",
  "departureTime": "12:00",
  "pricePerSeat": 5000,
  "availableSeats": 3,
  "vehicleModel": "Toyota Corolla",
  "vehicleColor": "White",
  "vehiclePlate": "SN123ABC"
}

@rideId = {{response.body.$.id}}

### Expected Response:
{
  "id": "ride123",
  "state": "PENDING",
  "driverId": ...
  "createdAt": "2026-03-18T10:00:00Z"
}

---

###
### PHASE 2: RÉSERVATION
###

### 4. Passager réserve trajet
POST http://localhost:3000/bookings
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @passengerToken

{
  "rideId": @rideId,
  "seats": 2,
  "passengerLat": 14.7167,
  "passengerLng": -17.4677,
  "message": "Très pressé!"
}

@bookingId = {{response.body.$.id}}
@securityCode = {{response.body.$.securityCode}}

### Expected Response:
{
  "id": "booking123",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "seats": 2,
  "securityCode": null  (sera généré à startRide)
}

---

### 5. Vérifier audit trail (Admin)
GET http://localhost:3000/rides/@rideId/events
Authorization: Bearer @adminToken

### Expected Events:
[
  { type: "CREATED", user: "chauffeur_test" }
  // Booking créée (logique application)
]

---

###
### PHASE 3: CONFIRMATION & DÉMARRAGE
###

### 6. Chauffeur confirme réservation (optionnel)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/bookings/@bookingId
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @driverToken

{
  "status": "CONFIRMED"
}

---

### 7. Chauffeur DÉMARRE le trajet 🟢
PATCH http://localhost:3000/rides/@rideId/start
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @driverToken

{
  "driverLat": 14.7167,
  "driverLng": -17.4677
}

### Expected Changes:
{
  "state": "IN_PROGRESS",           ← CHANGEMENT CLIÉ
  "actualStartTime": "2026-03-18T11:45:00Z"
}

### Booking Updated:
{
  "status": "CODE_SENT",             ← CHANGEMENT
  "securityCode": "5847",            ← GÉNÉRÉ
  "codeExpiry": "2026-03-18T12:15:00Z"  ← 30 minutes
}

---

### 8. Vérifier le code envoyé (audit)
GET http://localhost:3000/rides/@rideId/events
Authorization: Bearer @passengerToken

### Expected Events:
[
  { type: "CREATED", user: "chauffeur_test" },
  { type: "STARTED_BY_DRIVER", user: "chauffeur_test" },
  { type: "PASSENGER_CODE_SENT", user: "passager_test", data: { code: "5847" } }
]

---

###
### PHASE 4: GÉOLOCALISATION EN TEMPS RÉEL
###

### 9. Chauffeur envoie déjà localisation (simule deplacement)
POST http://localhost:3000/tracking/update-location/@rideId
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @driverToken

{
  "driverId": @driverId,
  "driverLat": 14.7200,
  "driverLng": -17.4650,
  "accuracy": 8.5,
  "heading": 270,
  "speed": 45.2
}

### Expected Response:
{
  "id": "tracking123",
  "rideId": @rideId,
  "driverLat": 14.7200,
  "driverLng": -17.4650,
  "timestamp": "2026-03-18T11:50:00Z"
}

---

### 10. Chauffeur UPDATE localisation (répéter 50x!)
POST http://localhost:3000/tracking/update-location/@rideId
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @driverToken

{
  "driverId": @driverId,
  "driverLat": 14.7250,  ← Nouvelle position
  "driverLng": -17.4600,  ← Nouvelle position
  "accuracy": 8.5,
  "heading": 270,
  "speed": 48.0
}

---

### 11. Passager regarde dernière position (WebSocket idealement)
GET http://localhost:3000/tracking/@rideId/latest
Authorization: Bearer @passengerToken

### Expected Response:
{
  "id": "tracking124",
  "driverLat": 14.7250,
  "driverLng": -17.4600,
  "timestamp": "2026-03-18T11:55:00Z"
}

---

### 12. Admin voit route complète
GET http://localhost:3000/tracking/@rideId/history
Authorization: Bearer @adminToken

### Expected Response (array):
[
  { lat: 14.7167, lng: -17.4677, timestamp: "11:45:00Z" },
  { lat: 14.7200, lng: -17.4650, timestamp: "11:50:00Z" },
  { lat: 14.7250, lng: -17.4600, timestamp: "11:55:00Z" },
  ...
]

---

###
### PHASE 5: VALIDATION CODE
###

### 13. Passager reçoit chauffeur et valide code ✅
PATCH http://localhost:3000/bookings/@bookingId/verify-code
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @passengerToken

{
  "code": "5847"  ← Le code reçu par SMS
}

### Expected Response:
{
  "status": "CODE_VERIFIED",         ← CHANGEMENT
  "codeVerifiedAt": "2026-03-18T12:10:00Z"
}

---

### 14. Vérifier événement validation
GET http://localhost:3000/rides/@rideId/events
Authorization: Bearer @passengerToken

### Expected New Event:
{ type: "PASSENGER_CODE_VERIFIED", user: "passager_test", timestamp: "12:10:00Z" }

---

###
### PHASE 6: FIN DU TRAJET
###

### 15. Chauffeur TERMINE le trajet 🏁
PATCH http://localhost:3000/rides/@rideId/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @driverToken

{}

### Expected Changes:
{
  "state": "COMPLETED",               ← CHANGEMENT
  "actualEndTime": "2026-03-18T12:25:00Z"
}

### Booking Updated:
{
  "status": "COMPLETED"               ← CHANGEMENT
}

---

